AGI - Thirteen police officers were arrested for mistreatment and torture in the 'Beccaria' juvenile prison in Milan.>&nbsp; The State Police and the Regional Investigative Nucleus for the Lombardy of the Penitentiary Police are carrying out an order with which the detention in prison has been placed against thirteen police officers, twelve of whom are still in service in the Penal Institute 'Cesare&nbsp;Beccaria' in Milan and the measure of the suspension from the exercise of public offices to the same staff. The offences at various levels challenged by the Prosecutor of the Republic from at least 2022 to the present day and committed against several detainees of minor age, are those of mistreatment in damage of minors, also through omission, aggravated by the disabled defence and abuse of power; contest in the crime of torture, even through omission, aggravated by the abuse of power of the official public and by the fact of having committed the fact in harm of minors; contest in the offence of minor injuries, even through omission, aggravated by the abyss and futile motives, the disabled and the abuse of power; contest in the crime of false ideology and an attempted sexual violence of an agent against a prisoner.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
"Coworkers have made a mistake, their behaviors are absolutely to censor, and my conviction is without if and without but. In prisons, everything's happening, and the situation is from 'saving who can'. There are also other responsibilities: It is not justified that you only pay the prison police, someone in the judicial administration should be ashamed and resign." He tells the AGI&nbsp;Aldo Di Giacomo>, secretary of the Penitentiary Police Syndicate (SPP), commenting on the arrest of the 13 agents.
&nbsp;
"Sgoments and unbelievers." Thus Gennarino De Fazio, Secretary of the Uilpa Penitentiary Police, defines the state of mind after the news of the arrests. "Of course we have unconditional trust in the pollutants, including the Penitentiary Police itself, and in the judiciary and we hope that you will soon shed full light on the incident - he adds -. Nevertheless, we call for the presumption of innocence and hope in our heart that the agents involved can prove the correctness of their work." &nbsp;&nbsp; The secretary of Uilpa underlines that, regardless of the outcome of the investigation, "the conclaimed dysfunctionality" of the prison system "does not guarantee nor guards nor 'guards', and indeed inactivates consciences by generating and nourishing violence and atrocities sometimes from both sides of the infiriate". "Now we will listen to the usual speeches of politicians and then turn off the reflections - he continues -. Immediate reforms and a prison decree with urgent procedures to secure the system. Between suicides, 32 inmates and 4 in agents since the beginning of the year, murders and violence, you can't leave anymore. Minister Carlo Nordio and the President of the Council Giorgia&nbsp;Meloni&nbsp; at least this time they avoid catwalks and immediately open a serious confrontation, we are as always ready to offer our contribution of ideas".&nbsp;
&nbsp;
For the mayor of Milan, Giuseppe Sala, > "il&nbsp;Beccaria&nbsp; was abandoned for years and years, without a direction. So it's clear that certain things can happen. They can, but they shouldn't. We'll see what's coming out of this investigation."

